body:
@xiarixiaoyao I follow your tip about hoodie.clustering.plan.strategy.max.bytes.per.group and use your patch from pr 4178 and the job now took 15 minutes, it is a good improvement.

<img width="1780" alt="Captura de Tela 2021-12-02 às 10 52 40" src="https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/36298331/144435131-bf8fbf38-d4af-4397-823e-5c3304d44dda.png">

Both tasks were submited at the same time.

it probably means the table you have is at verson 0 or 1. but the bulk insert you performed is with 0.9.0 (version 2). 

```java
public enum HoodieTableVersion {
  // < 0.6.0 versions
  ZERO(0),
  // 0.6.0 onwards
  ONE(1),
  // 0.9.0 onwards
  TWO(2),
  // 0.10.0 onwards
  THREE(3);
```

You can try CLI command (using 0.9.0) to perform upgrade or downgrade on the table. `org.apache.hudi.cli.commands.UpgradeOrDowngradeCommand`

you can choose to stay with version 2 or 1 onwards
